{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778979904686,"sessionID":"ses_1cc8aab39ffe03EkBuu7cY5Ao7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_xAWKcHEX81n4YW2Ks84m8TWz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Updated `dorsolateral prefrontal cortex` (`UBERON:0009834`) so it is `part_of` `prefrontal cortex` (`UBERON:0000451`) rather than directly `part_of` `cerebral cortex`, following the issue discussion and Allen Brain Atlas-based guidance.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated the parentage of `UBERON:0009834` (`dorsolateral prefrontal cortex`) to match the requested anatomical hierarchy from issue #3447.\n+\n+What changed:\n+- Replaced `relationship: part_of UBERON:0000956 ! cerebral cortex`\n+- With `relationship: part_of UBERON:0000451 ! prefrontal cortex`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue discussion requested tightening this relationship so `dorsolateral prefrontal cortex` sits under `prefrontal cortex` rather than as a sibling-level regional part of `cerebral cortex`.\n+- `prefrontal cortex` is already modeled as `part_of cerebral cortex`, so this preserves the broader placement while making the immediate parent more specific.\n+- This matches the guidance cited in the issue discussion from the Allen Brain Atlas.\n+\n+Validation performed:\n+- Read the imported issue context and comments in `__issue_context__.json`.\n+- Confirmed the current stanzas for `UBERON:0009834` and `UBERON:0000451` in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Edited the term via the standard checkout/checkin workflow (`obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl`).\n+- Reserialized the ontology with `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Reviewed the resulting diff to confirm the only ontology change was the intended `part_of` target update.\n+\n+Completed c